---
applyTo: "tests/**/*.py,**/test_*.py,**/*_test.py"
---

When editing Python tests:

- Test observable behavior instead of private implementation details where practical.
- Add regression coverage for the exact bug or edge case being changed.
- Prefer parametrization over copy-pasted cases.
- Avoid wall-clock sleeps, network calls, and nondeterministic randomness unless the repository already requires them.
